AB  - Since its inception in 1990,The Journal of Financial Intermediationhas striven to be a high-quality outlet for empirical and theoretical research in financial intermediation, market microstructure, and corporate finance. This article briefly reviews the output of theJournalsince its inception, describes recent changes, and takes a look at the future.
